The paper proposes a design of a hierarchical fuzzy inference tree (HFIT) using multiobjective genetic programming and differential evolution algorithms. The HFIT is evaluated through six application problems and compared with other FISs methods from the literature. The paper's focus on optimization and machine learning techniques suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The use of the HFIT for system control and decision-making also suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of multiobjective programming and optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-category.
